WEBVTT

00:05.698 --> 00:08.200
<i>The two men
who looked most pleased tonight</i>

00:08.200 --> 00:10.119
<i>were President Nixon
and Brezhnev,</i>

00:10.119 --> 00:12.455
<i>and well they might,
since both have prevailed</i>

00:12.455 --> 00:13.998
<i>over groups
in their own countries</i>

00:13.998 --> 00:15.624
<i>who think
an arms limitation deal</i>

00:15.624 --> 00:17.042
<i>is wicked folly.</i>

00:17.042 --> 00:19.754
<i>What was signed tonight
was the result of risks,</i>

00:19.754 --> 00:22.548
<i>time, patience,
and political skill.</i>

00:22.548 --> 00:24.425
<i>The signing ceremony
for the agreements</i>

00:24.425 --> 00:25.926
<i>on nuclear weapons...</i>

00:25.926 --> 00:28.554
<i>Unit Two to Unit Three. Come in.</i>

00:30.055 --> 00:33.267
<i>Unit Two to Unit Three.
Request status report. Over.</i>

00:35.478 --> 00:39.440
Unit Three to Unit Two.
Roger that. Gimme a sec. Over.

00:39.440 --> 00:41.776
<i>...so it all went
well in Vladimir's hall</i>

00:41.776 --> 00:42.985
<i>in the Kremlin tonight.</i>

00:42.985 --> 00:45.362
<i>And if Mr. Nixon didn't make
any new friends,</i>

00:45.362 --> 00:47.948
<i>his enemies looked
less dangerous.</i>

00:47.948 --> 00:49.492
<i>And as far as the history</i>

00:49.492 --> 00:51.035
<i>of the nuclear age
is concerned...</i>

00:51.035 --> 00:54.622
Unit Three to Units One and Two.
Chickens are in the henhouse.

00:54.622 --> 00:56.999
Over.
Copy that.

00:56.999 --> 01:01.170
Copy that.
Passing the entrance now. Over.

01:01.170 --> 01:03.297
<i>Unit Two, where are you going?</i>

01:03.297 --> 01:05.800
<i>Why are you passing
the entrance to the henhouse?</i>

01:05.800 --> 01:08.344
There's a 24-hour guard
in the lobby,

01:08.344 --> 01:10.471
so I found us a back door.

01:10.471 --> 01:14.975
Back door?
Uh, Unit Two, what back door?

01:15.726 --> 01:21.023
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

01:21.023 --> 01:23.317
What the fuck
are we doing here?

01:23.317 --> 01:24.610
You'll see.

01:24.610 --> 01:26.821
Good evening, gentlemen.
Welcome to the Watergate Hotel.

01:32.284 --> 01:33.953
This way.

01:38.415 --> 01:40.584
Lucky for us,
the complex contains

01:40.584 --> 01:43.295
six different buildings,
all interconnected,

01:43.295 --> 01:46.090
so we can
bypass lobby security.

01:47.091 --> 01:48.342
Good evening, gentlemen.

01:48.342 --> 01:50.928
Welcome to the Watergate Office Building,

01:50.928 --> 01:54.723
home of the Democratic
National Committee.

01:54.723 --> 01:56.225
Very nice, boss.

02:00.271 --> 02:01.897
- Hey. Down.
- Down?

02:01.897 --> 02:03.524
Down.

02:08.320 --> 02:11.574
Unit Three to Unit Two.
Hold your position. Over.

02:11.574 --> 02:14.326
Worry not.
I found us the perfect place

02:14.326 --> 02:16.412
to hide and wait
on the banquet level.

02:16.412 --> 02:18.163
Unit Two,
where the hell are you gonna

02:18.163 --> 02:19.707
hide on the banquet level?

02:19.707 --> 02:22.334
<i>Simple, I booked a banquet room.</i>

02:23.168 --> 02:24.295
♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

02:24.295 --> 02:28.048
Good evening, gentlemen.
Welcome to the Continental Room.

02:28.048 --> 02:30.092
We are the Ameritas party.

02:30.634 --> 02:32.011
- We are?
- Yeah.

02:32.011 --> 02:33.679
- We are.
- We are.

02:33.679 --> 02:35.264
♪ (THEME MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

02:42.271 --> 02:44.315
♪ (THEME MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

02:44.315 --> 02:45.858
So, tell me, gentlemen.

02:45.858 --> 02:48.110
what does
the Ameritas Corporation do?

02:48.110 --> 02:50.279
- What?
- ♪ (SOFT MUSIC PLAYING
OVER SPEAKER) ♪

02:53.115 --> 02:55.075
- Business!
- Huh.

02:55.075 --> 02:56.535
- Business.
- What kind of business?

02:58.037 --> 02:59.538
Uh, transportation.

02:59.538 --> 03:01.790
Transportation.

03:01.790 --> 03:03.626
Bon appétit!

03:03.626 --> 03:05.085
How come you got soup?

03:06.045 --> 03:08.088
Because it was soup or salad.

03:09.173 --> 03:10.633
I thought it was soup and salad.

03:10.633 --> 03:11.634
<i>Oye.</i>

03:14.345 --> 03:17.264
- Oh.
- Say, Frank.

03:17.264 --> 03:20.559
Bet you killed quite a few Japs
in the war?

03:21.310 --> 03:22.561
I ain't one to brag.

03:22.561 --> 03:25.272
Why don't you ask him
about the couple of dozen guys

03:25.272 --> 03:26.607
he greased for Castro

03:26.607 --> 03:29.151
before he realized
the bearded shitbird

03:29.151 --> 03:32.071
was giving Khrushchev
a courtesy reach-around.

03:32.071 --> 03:33.280
Oh!

03:33.280 --> 03:35.991
You know,
I wasn't the only company man

03:35.991 --> 03:38.619
to get outsmarted
by Fidel, Eduardo.

03:39.411 --> 03:41.789
Your hands are as dirty as mine.

03:41.789 --> 03:43.332
Thank you.
What the shit!

03:43.332 --> 03:45.876
- You got another soup?
- I ordered it.

03:45.876 --> 03:47.002
Can I get another soup?

03:47.002 --> 03:49.213
Oh, very sorry, sir.
That was the last one.

03:52.132 --> 03:53.801
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

03:53.801 --> 03:56.762
Gentlemen, thank you, uh,
you can clear out now,

03:56.762 --> 04:00.182
uh, we're going to stay,
maybe have a couple of stogies.

04:00.182 --> 04:02.351
Uh... Oh.

04:02.351 --> 04:04.561
You're way ahead of me.
Thank you so much.

04:04.561 --> 04:06.146
Thank you, sir.
- Have a good night.

04:06.146 --> 04:07.272
You, too.

04:09.608 --> 04:11.735
- Gordon.
- Gentlemen.

04:12.695 --> 04:13.988
It's 10:00 p.m.

04:13.988 --> 04:15.656
Unit Two will head up
to the DNC,

04:15.656 --> 04:18.909
my team will meet our guy
at the McGovern HQ.

04:18.909 --> 04:21.036
Come on.

04:22.246 --> 04:26.291
Villo.

04:27.418 --> 04:30.504
Remember.
Photograph everything.

04:30.504 --> 04:32.089
Right, boss. Just like Fielding.

04:33.507 --> 04:36.677
No. Not like Fielding.

04:36.677 --> 04:38.512
Wait for Baldwin's signal,
then head up.

04:38.512 --> 04:40.389
Roger that.
- Come on.

04:40.389 --> 04:42.099
Unit Two to Unit Three.

04:42.099 --> 04:44.184
What's happening
in the henhouse? Over.

04:44.184 --> 04:50.065
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

04:54.653 --> 04:57.823
- ♪ (TENSE MUSIC PLAYING) ♪
- That's the place.

04:57.823 --> 05:00.409
My inside man
in the McGovern campaign said

05:00.409 --> 05:01.952
wait by the back door.

05:01.952 --> 05:04.038
Well, it is pretty
damn bright back there.

05:04.747 --> 05:05.998
I can fix that.

05:18.510 --> 05:19.887
♪ (MUSIC FADES) ♪

05:22.514 --> 05:24.433
Tricky angle.

05:24.433 --> 05:25.809
Did you serve?

05:25.809 --> 05:29.396
I did. But I missed out
on all the action.

05:29.396 --> 05:33.317
In basic training,
before we shipped out to Korea,

05:33.317 --> 05:34.818
some of the fellows
challenged me

05:34.818 --> 05:36.278
to a sit-up contest.

05:37.446 --> 05:40.365
I won the contest,
but blew my appendix.

05:42.534 --> 05:44.286
Still haunts me.

05:46.205 --> 05:48.373
Don't worry. I'll get it.

05:48.373 --> 05:50.959
Maybe it's your appendix.

05:50.959 --> 05:54.922
Unit Three to Unit Two.
Henhouse status unchanged.

05:54.922 --> 05:58.717
- That's a no-go. Over.
- Copy that. Over.

06:10.354 --> 06:12.022
Very close.

06:14.525 --> 06:15.692
Please, stop swaying!

06:15.692 --> 06:18.737
I wouldn't be swaying
if you made the fucking shot.

06:21.406 --> 06:23.826
Almost, Halcón.

06:23.826 --> 06:24.827
What's "Halcón"?

06:24.827 --> 06:27.121
His nickname.
It means "the falcon."

06:27.121 --> 06:30.541
The bird all other birds fear.

06:30.541 --> 06:33.377
Shouldn't it be "halcon"
like "falcon"?

06:33.377 --> 06:34.378
No.

06:35.504 --> 06:37.798
Nice shot, Halcón.

06:37.798 --> 06:39.633
Come on.
Help me down.

06:39.633 --> 06:41.385
"Halcon" really sounds better.

06:42.427 --> 06:43.762
<i>Coño.</i>

06:43.762 --> 06:46.306
- What the hell
is going on up there?
<i>- No lo sé.</i>

06:48.183 --> 06:49.601
Um, sir,

06:49.601 --> 06:51.061
the manager said
you gentlemen were supposed

06:51.061 --> 06:52.396
to be done here by 10:00.
Indeed.

06:52.396 --> 06:56.066
We are just packing up
the, uh, projector,

06:56.066 --> 06:58.777
and then we will be on our way.
Scout's honor.

06:58.777 --> 07:01.113
No problem,
just gotta lock up by midnight.

07:01.530 --> 07:02.531
Bye!

07:09.496 --> 07:12.916
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

07:20.090 --> 07:23.427
Fan out. See,
this means fan out.

07:23.427 --> 07:25.804
It's too dark in here.
I can't see shit.

07:26.180 --> 07:27.222
Criminy!

07:32.269 --> 07:33.896
Where the hell is he?

07:33.896 --> 07:35.439
♪ (MUSIC FADES) ♪

07:35.439 --> 07:38.650
Don't worry.

07:38.650 --> 07:40.777
My guy's a professional.
He'll be here.

07:43.655 --> 07:46.033
Excuse me.

07:47.993 --> 07:49.244
Hi.
What?

07:49.244 --> 07:52.414
You are our inside man!
What are you doing outside?

07:52.414 --> 07:53.790
The janitor found me!

07:53.790 --> 07:55.834
I was hiding
in the furnace room.

07:55.834 --> 07:56.919
He got scared. The kid,

07:56.919 --> 07:58.462
he must have come out
the front door.

07:58.462 --> 08:00.339
Get back to your post!

08:00.339 --> 08:03.008
I don't think I'm cut out
for this stuff, sir.

08:03.008 --> 08:05.052
I'm sorry.
Fuck!

08:05.052 --> 08:08.972
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

08:08.972 --> 08:10.641
You gutless Mormon!

08:14.061 --> 08:15.229
Your guy, huh?

08:22.027 --> 08:25.614
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

08:38.585 --> 08:41.129
<i>Unit Two,
the henhouse is nearly empty.</i>

08:41.129 --> 08:43.632
<i>Repeat Three to Two.
Henhouse is nearly empty.</i>

08:43.632 --> 08:45.884
<i>Get into position, over.</i>

08:48.637 --> 08:51.056
<i>Vámonos, vámonos.</i>

08:58.438 --> 09:00.232
It's locked.

09:00.232 --> 09:02.484
<i>- Señor</i> Locksmith.
- Okay.

09:05.904 --> 09:07.614
<i>¡Puñeta!</i>

09:07.614 --> 09:11.159
You didn't tell me
it was a double-sided deadbolt.

09:11.159 --> 09:13.787
Are you saying we're locked in?

09:19.167 --> 09:21.336
<i>¡Puta madre! ¡Coño!</i>

09:23.797 --> 09:25.299
Back to the closet.

09:28.510 --> 09:29.761
<i>¡Cállate!</i>

09:30.721 --> 09:32.681
♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

09:35.058 --> 09:36.560
<i>Oye, chico.</i>

09:36.560 --> 09:38.895
I guess we're sleeping here.

09:38.895 --> 09:40.814
Nighty night.

09:42.190 --> 09:46.236
How was your steak?
I didn't eat steak.

09:46.236 --> 09:48.572
I had the tilapia.

09:48.572 --> 09:50.699
How was it?
It was okay.

09:52.075 --> 09:54.244
Oh, Christ.
I gotta take a leak.

10:16.600 --> 10:18.185
Oh.

10:23.273 --> 10:25.484
<i>Muy necesito.</i>

10:26.985 --> 10:29.446
<i>Three to Two. Henhouse is empty.</i>

10:29.446 --> 10:31.698
<i>All clear. Proceed. Over.</i>

10:34.951 --> 10:36.828
Here.
<i>Hello.</i>

10:40.248 --> 10:41.833
I repeat, all clear.

10:41.833 --> 10:43.960
Unit Two, proceed. Over.

10:46.254 --> 10:47.255
<i>Hello?</i>

10:49.925 --> 10:51.093
<i>Unit Two?</i>

10:52.344 --> 10:54.429
<i>Anyone there?</i>

10:56.098 --> 10:57.891
<i>And here it is.
Thirteen minutes before six.</i>

10:57.891 --> 10:59.309
<i>A beautiful morning.
And a good time</i>

10:59.309 --> 11:01.812
<i>to check on the traffic here
with traffic officer, Bill.</i>

11:01.812 --> 11:03.480
<i>The traffic
is quite considerably</i>

11:03.480 --> 11:05.899
<i>moving nicely into
the Downtown DC area.</i>

11:05.899 --> 11:08.110
<i>Folks will be glad to hear that.</i>

11:13.365 --> 11:14.783
<i>Okay, Officer Bill.
Thank you.</i>

11:14.783 --> 11:17.035
<i>Well, actually, we have
another traffic update</i>

11:17.035 --> 11:18.620
<i>and the weather forecast
and we just...</i>

11:29.339 --> 11:33.844
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

11:44.855 --> 11:46.022
Whatever you do,

11:46.022 --> 11:49.192
do not drink the whiskey
at the Watergate.

11:50.902 --> 11:53.989
Hmm. Roger that.

11:59.619 --> 12:00.746
Papa?

12:01.746 --> 12:03.039
Papa?

12:06.710 --> 12:07.752
Kevan?

12:08.753 --> 12:12.674
Yes, my... sweet angel?

12:13.300 --> 12:14.551
Who's Gordon Liddy?

12:17.095 --> 12:18.597
Wait,
we're gonna do everything.

12:18.597 --> 12:20.682
Well, the lube
is gonna soak--
- Morning.

12:21.516 --> 12:22.601
Howard.

12:23.894 --> 12:26.938
No one woke me for breakfast.

12:26.938 --> 12:30.400
Well, Howard, we never know
what your plans are.

12:30.400 --> 12:33.195
We're headed to the club
for a swim and some tennis.

12:33.195 --> 12:35.238
Assuming you've paid the bill.

12:37.616 --> 12:41.119
She's a funny one.

12:43.580 --> 12:45.540
- You didn't see me.
- Okay.

12:46.208 --> 12:48.543
Eggs?
Yeah.

12:48.543 --> 12:50.086
Did you see the Viet Cong
come through here?

12:50.086 --> 12:52.839
No VC were invited
for breakfast.

12:52.839 --> 12:54.007
Uh, went that way, honey.

12:55.258 --> 12:57.135
You got it.
Oh! Uh...

12:57.135 --> 13:00.931
Kevan is our resident Smithie.
Home for the holiday.

13:00.931 --> 13:02.599
4.0 grade average.

13:02.599 --> 13:06.061
Well, maybe if you two applied
yourselves a little more.

13:06.061 --> 13:08.063
Oh. Maybe if you

13:08.063 --> 13:09.814
applied yourself
a little bit more.

13:09.814 --> 13:11.024
Yeah.

13:11.024 --> 13:14.069
Well, actually, she's right.
Especially you, boy.

13:14.069 --> 13:15.278
Oh.

13:15.278 --> 13:19.324
Dorothy was telling me
about your big Paris trip.

13:19.324 --> 13:23.453
Oh. Well. Uh, about that.
I'm-- I'm not sure we're going

13:23.453 --> 13:26.122
to be able to vacation
this summer.

13:26.122 --> 13:27.791
Might be busy with Gordon.

13:28.333 --> 13:29.751
<i>Muy busy-oso.</i>

13:29.751 --> 13:31.419
Don't worry about Paris, dear.

13:31.419 --> 13:33.296
It's just gonna be me,
and David, and Kevan.

13:34.381 --> 13:38.009
Oh. Good. Fun.

13:38.009 --> 13:40.595
Well, I have
some really exciting news.

13:40.595 --> 13:43.098
I finally figured out
what I want to do with my life.

13:43.098 --> 13:44.182
Oh?

13:44.182 --> 13:46.643
I am going to be a farmer.

13:48.144 --> 13:51.231
- A... As in crops and dirt?
- That is noble work.

13:51.231 --> 13:53.233
Great. All that tuition
right down--

13:53.233 --> 13:54.693
Eat lead, Charlie!

13:55.777 --> 13:56.945
Oh, my God!

13:56.945 --> 13:58.738
Put that down.
He's just a child with a toy.

13:58.738 --> 14:01.491
Gordon, Gordon. Uh,
let's get some air.

14:01.491 --> 14:02.826
Come on. Outside.

14:04.869 --> 14:06.621
Oh, my God.

14:06.621 --> 14:10.000
That toy gun is a recipe
for disaster.

14:10.000 --> 14:12.127
Only real guns
in the Liddy household.

14:12.127 --> 14:16.047
I do not need
child-rearing lessons from you.

14:16.047 --> 14:18.300
<i>- Danke schön.</i>
- Come on.

14:22.012 --> 14:23.847
We should get
the wives together again.

14:23.847 --> 14:25.765
Fran has been asking.

14:25.765 --> 14:29.102
Oh, yes.
Dorothy would love that.

14:29.102 --> 14:32.397
McGovern HQ has added
round-the-clock security.

14:32.397 --> 14:34.441
so that just leaves
the Watergate.

14:35.483 --> 14:37.277
We strike tonight.

14:37.277 --> 14:39.321
We walk straight
in the front door.

14:39.321 --> 14:43.116
No more bullshit banquets,
just sheer force of will.

14:43.867 --> 14:45.619
That's not a plan!

14:45.619 --> 14:48.330
What's our cover?
We're all with the DNC

14:48.330 --> 14:49.998
and we forgot our wallets?

14:53.418 --> 14:56.463
<i>Gefunden!</i> That's our way in.

14:56.463 --> 14:58.548
Buying a new briefcase, are we?

14:59.549 --> 15:00.967
Move along.

15:00.967 --> 15:04.054
We are going to talk
about this farming business.

15:04.054 --> 15:05.930
It's called agriculture.

15:08.308 --> 15:09.351
Look.

15:10.352 --> 15:12.479
We are there
for a different meeting

15:12.479 --> 15:16.775
in another office.
On another floor, all together.

15:16.775 --> 15:18.693
Did you okay this with Magruder?

15:18.693 --> 15:21.821
Hell no. Magruder has no idea
about last night's debacle.

15:21.821 --> 15:23.031
If we go in tonight,

15:23.031 --> 15:25.075
it's as though last night
never even happened.

15:25.075 --> 15:26.576
As far as anyone knows,

15:26.576 --> 15:29.788
tonight will be
our first attempt.

15:33.291 --> 15:39.589
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

15:45.679 --> 15:47.681
Can I help you?
We have an appointment.

15:48.390 --> 15:50.016
Federal Reserve Office.

15:50.016 --> 15:51.851
- Eighth floor.
- At midnight.

15:51.851 --> 15:53.395
Middle of Memorial Day Weekend?

15:53.395 --> 15:55.021
International business.

15:55.980 --> 15:57.732
You know, time zones.

15:58.692 --> 15:59.943
All right. Sign in.

16:17.836 --> 16:19.421
<i>Rápido, amigos. Rápido.</i>

16:39.649 --> 16:42.902
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

16:42.902 --> 16:44.654
Where the hell is McCord?

16:45.697 --> 16:46.698
What?

16:47.866 --> 16:49.993
<i>That son of a bitch
has the equipment.</i>

16:49.993 --> 16:52.370
<i>I knew that oddball
would go rogue!</i>

16:52.370 --> 16:53.997
- I knew it!
- I know.

17:00.962 --> 17:02.756
Villo. <i>¿Qué pasa?</i>

17:02.756 --> 17:04.215
These are the wrong tools.

17:04.215 --> 17:05.425
What?

17:05.425 --> 17:08.887
He has the wrong tools.
How is that even possible?

17:08.887 --> 17:11.431
- I have right tools!
- He has the right tools.

17:12.015 --> 17:12.807
In Miami.

17:12.807 --> 17:14.267
BERNARD "MACHO" BARKER: <i>¿Dónde?</i>

17:14.267 --> 17:17.312
♪ (TENSE MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

17:17.312 --> 17:19.105
Hey!
What the...

17:21.357 --> 17:23.234
- Larry?
- Jim?

17:23.234 --> 17:25.278
You scared the shit out of me.
What are you doing here?

17:25.278 --> 17:28.156
I got a meeting
at the Federal Reserve.

17:28.156 --> 17:31.117
Looks like my guy didn't show.

17:31.117 --> 17:32.827
I'll give him another 45 minutes
or so.

17:32.827 --> 17:34.829
I'll just wait
on the couch there.

17:34.829 --> 17:39.000
Ed, this is Jim McCord.
John Mitchell's bodyguard.

17:39.000 --> 17:42.462
No, not anymore. Huh.
No, I started my own firm.

17:42.462 --> 17:45.340
Doing some contract work
with the Committee to Re-Elect.

17:46.216 --> 17:47.217
Really?

17:48.384 --> 17:50.094
- You guys hiring?
- Definitely.

17:51.888 --> 17:56.351
I want to know everything
that you said to them.

17:57.310 --> 17:58.812
- Verbatim!
- But I don't remember

17:58.812 --> 18:00.355
every damn word
they said to me, Gordon.

18:00.355 --> 18:01.689
I was trying
to keep them occupied!

18:01.689 --> 18:03.358
I warned you about him!
I predicted this.

18:03.358 --> 18:05.235
Warned him about what?

18:05.235 --> 18:08.404
What did you warn him about,
Gordon? No! Gordon!

18:08.404 --> 18:11.449
This is a Cuban locksmith
who can't pick a lock.

18:11.449 --> 18:13.535
Sandwiches, gentlemen?

18:14.911 --> 18:16.663
Turkey, ham, tuna fish.

18:16.663 --> 18:18.581
ROLANDO "MUSCULITO" MARTINEZ:
<i>Muchas gracias,</i> Dorothy.

18:21.042 --> 18:23.044
I'll leave you boys to it.

18:23.044 --> 18:24.170
Thank you.

18:27.257 --> 18:29.300
- And you...
- Uh...

18:29.300 --> 18:31.177
<i>-¿Sí?</i>
- You, <i>señor,</i>

18:31.177 --> 18:32.804
are on the first flight back

18:32.804 --> 18:34.722
- to Miami.
- Okay.

18:34.722 --> 18:36.224
And you're going to collect
the right tools

18:36.224 --> 18:38.017
and you're coming back here tonight.

18:38.017 --> 18:40.895
And we're all going in again.

18:40.895 --> 18:44.816
We cannot break in
a third time, Gordon.

18:45.942 --> 18:48.945
We have not broken in once!

18:54.075 --> 18:57.370
Bernard. I have
a little something for Clara.

18:57.370 --> 18:59.038
<i>Ay, gracias,</i> Dorothy.

19:04.669 --> 19:06.462
<i>-Muchas gracias.
- De nada.</i>

19:06.462 --> 19:09.716
♪ (SOFT MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

19:10.717 --> 19:12.635
- Dorothy.
- Gordon.

19:17.974 --> 19:19.893
So, what's the plan?

19:19.893 --> 19:23.396
Uh, we're going in
through the garage this time.

19:23.396 --> 19:25.148
- ♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪
- Here you go.

19:25.148 --> 19:28.234
<i>Delivery guys are in
and out of there all day.</i>
- Thanks, Cap.

19:28.234 --> 19:29.944
<i>Always taping the lock open.</i>

19:29.944 --> 19:32.238
<i>So no one should notice.</i>

19:32.238 --> 19:35.283
<i>McCord is going to take care
of the door.</i>

19:36.200 --> 19:37.785
<i>This is our last chance.</i>

19:37.785 --> 19:40.914
What I meant was are you taking
Kevan to the train station

19:40.914 --> 19:42.248
or should I ask St. John?

19:42.248 --> 19:44.459
I-- I think
you just answered my question.

19:44.459 --> 19:47.003
Oh. But it's the long weekend.

19:47.003 --> 19:49.047
Remember, Papa,
I have a sociology paper

19:49.047 --> 19:52.300
due on Tuesday. I told you
I was leaving today.

19:52.300 --> 19:55.261
Well, can't--
can't you wait another day?

19:55.261 --> 19:56.971
I barely got
to spend time with you.

19:56.971 --> 19:58.723
Well, whose fault is that?

19:59.849 --> 20:00.934
I wish I could.

20:02.352 --> 20:04.562
Come on, sis.
We're going to be late.

20:04.562 --> 20:06.981
- Okay. Bye.
- Bye.

20:08.107 --> 20:09.817
Bye, Papa.

20:10.902 --> 20:11.945
Bye, kiddo.

20:12.779 --> 20:13.863
Bye.

20:16.240 --> 20:18.368
You're going in tonight?
For God's sake,

20:18.368 --> 20:20.578
the president just signed
the SALT treaty.

20:20.578 --> 20:21.829
He's far ahead in the polls.

20:21.829 --> 20:23.915
Is any of this nickel-and-dime,
cloak-and-dagger stuff

20:23.915 --> 20:25.249
necessary?

20:25.249 --> 20:29.796
We can't afford to take chances
with the future of democracy.

20:29.796 --> 20:33.299
Ergo, in through
the garage we go.

20:33.299 --> 20:34.801
Howard,
that is the stupidest thing

20:34.801 --> 20:37.929
I've ever heard.
Please take a minute

20:37.929 --> 20:40.056
to reconsider
what you're about to do.

20:45.812 --> 20:47.730
<i>Now here comes
the president's helicopter,</i>

20:47.730 --> 20:50.733
<i>Marine Helicopter Number One,
landing in the plaza</i>

20:50.733 --> 20:51.943
<i>on the east side</i>

20:51.943 --> 20:53.695
<i>of the east front
of the Capitol.</i>

20:53.695 --> 20:57.031
<i>Arriving almost exactly...
exactly as scheduled</i>

20:57.031 --> 21:01.452
<i>at 9:30, at the Capitol plaza,
so that he can go up the steps</i>

21:01.452 --> 21:04.205
<i>of the House of Representatives,
go into the chamber,</i>

21:04.205 --> 21:07.000
<i>and address the members
of the House, of the Senate,</i>

21:07.000 --> 21:09.043
<i>Supreme Court,
the Diplomatic Corps</i>

21:09.043 --> 21:11.379
<i>of Washington,
all of whom are inside</i>

21:11.379 --> 21:12.672
<i>waiting for him
in the chamber</i>

21:12.672 --> 21:14.465
<i>of the House of Representatives.</i>

21:17.093 --> 21:20.179
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

21:28.771 --> 21:30.565
We're on the second floor.

21:30.565 --> 21:33.276
<i>NBC News presents
the last in its series</i>

21:33.276 --> 21:35.445
<i>of programs
on President Nixon's journey</i>

21:35.445 --> 21:38.323
<i>to Russia.
Brought to you by Shell,</i>

21:38.323 --> 21:41.534
<i>Super Shell and non-leaded Shell
of the Future.</i>

21:41.534 --> 21:45.163
♪ (MUSIC CONTINUES) ♪

21:59.260 --> 22:03.056
What?
Just making sure
you're here.

22:03.056 --> 22:05.391
<i>Mr. Speaker,</i>

22:05.391 --> 22:08.269
<i>the President of United States.</i>

22:20.114 --> 22:21.532
<i>My fellow Americans,</i>

22:21.532 --> 22:23.659
<i>your welcome
in this great chamber tonight</i>

22:23.659 --> 22:27.955
<i>has a very special meaning
to Mrs. Nixon and to me.</i>

22:29.332 --> 22:30.374
<i>We can be proud</i>

22:30.374 --> 22:34.128
<i>that we now have
an historic opportunity</i>

22:34.128 --> 22:40.259
<i>to play a great role in helping
to achieve man's oldest dream.</i>

22:40.259 --> 22:42.303
<i>A world in which all nations</i>

22:42.303 --> 22:44.680
<i>can enjoy the blessings
of peace.</i>

22:45.848 --> 22:50.394
<i>An unparalleled opportunity
has been placed</i>

22:50.394 --> 22:52.105
<i>in America's hands.</i>

22:53.356 --> 22:56.609
<i>We can seize this moment
or we can lose it.</i>

22:57.860 --> 22:59.320
<i>We can make good
this opportunity</i>

22:59.320 --> 23:02.281
<i>to build a new structure
of peace in the world.</i>

23:02.281 --> 23:05.326
<i>Or we can let it slip away.</i>

23:05.326 --> 23:07.954
<i>Let us seize the moment
so that our children</i>

23:07.954 --> 23:09.831
<i>and the world's children</i>

23:09.831 --> 23:13.626
<i>can live free of the fears
and free of the hatreds</i>

23:13.626 --> 23:15.753
<i>that have been the lot
of mankind</i>

23:15.753 --> 23:17.463
<i>through the centuries.</i>

23:17.463 --> 23:20.216
It's two bedrooms,
near the beach.

23:20.216 --> 23:21.968
<i>For America to continue...</i>

23:21.968 --> 23:23.219
It's a steal.

23:23.219 --> 23:27.306
I'm not looking to buy a house
in Miami.

23:27.306 --> 23:30.143
<i>...we must keep America
number one</i>

23:30.143 --> 23:31.894
<i>economically in the world.</i>

23:31.894 --> 23:36.983
What about split level?
Jacksonville?

23:36.983 --> 23:38.276
<i>...we must keep America...</i>

23:38.276 --> 23:40.153
- What?
- Maybe.

23:40.153 --> 23:45.783
<i>And then the historians
will write of the year 1972</i>

23:45.783 --> 23:50.788
<i>that this was the year
when America helped to lead</i>

23:50.788 --> 23:54.125
<i>the world up
out of the lowlands</i>

23:54.125 --> 23:59.505
<i>of constant war
and onto the high plateau</i>

23:59.505 --> 24:03.593
<i>of lasting peace.</i>

24:13.769 --> 24:16.981
♪ (MUSIC FADES) ♪

24:24.697 --> 24:30.036
♪ (SINGING IN SPANISH) ♪

24:30.786 --> 24:36.250
♪ (SINGING CONTINUES) ♪

24:36.250 --> 24:39.295
<i>¡Viva Nixon!</i>

24:39.295 --> 24:41.756
Fuck Kennedy!
Fuck Kennedy!

24:44.717 --> 24:46.219
You know, I'll bet you,

24:46.219 --> 24:49.013
we could sell Dean
on Project SAPPHIRE right now.

24:49.013 --> 24:50.765
- Maybe even TOPAZ.
- Why stop there?

24:50.765 --> 24:52.141
All the gemstones!

24:52.141 --> 24:54.560
We'll open a goddamn
jewelry store!

24:54.560 --> 24:56.395
All the gemstones!

24:56.395 --> 24:57.939
Commie simps
aren't going to know

24:57.939 --> 24:59.649
what hit them.

24:59.649 --> 25:01.442
You know,
by the time this is over,

25:01.442 --> 25:03.361
we will be able
to write our own ticket.

25:03.361 --> 25:04.487
- Two? Uh-huh.
- Yeah.

25:04.487 --> 25:07.615
Come with me.
- Hey! Jim! Fred!

25:07.615 --> 25:09.825
Uh, hi.
It's Howard!

25:15.414 --> 25:16.916
Hunt.
Ah.

25:16.916 --> 25:19.293
Staying busy over at Mullen,
I trust.

25:19.293 --> 25:22.588
Uh, actually, I've been working
for the White House.

25:22.588 --> 25:24.715
Uh, doing some exciting stuff.

25:26.300 --> 25:28.678
So I hear. Yeah.

25:28.678 --> 25:32.223
Uh... Uh, this is, uh,
Fred Jessup.

25:32.223 --> 25:34.850
- Uh, this is
my good friend, Gord--
- Walter. Walter.

25:34.850 --> 25:36.435
Can you call Lewis
about Saturday?

25:36.435 --> 25:40.106
We still need a fourth.
Nine a.m. tee time. Thanks.

25:40.690 --> 25:42.400
You know, not to boast,

25:42.400 --> 25:48.197
but, uh, I'm
a ten handicap myself, nearly.

25:48.197 --> 25:52.118
Well, we...
We, uh, play Chevy Chase.

25:52.118 --> 25:54.620
Uh, Club tourney, members only.

25:55.538 --> 25:56.664
Of course. Of course.

25:56.664 --> 25:58.916
- I-- I wasn't offering.
- Good to see you, Howard.

25:59.750 --> 26:01.877
Yes. See you, Fred.

26:03.754 --> 26:06.007
So, that's Angleton, eh?

26:06.882 --> 26:08.801
Snake-hipped son of a bitch.

26:10.261 --> 26:12.638
Is it true about him
and Mary Meyer?

26:12.638 --> 26:14.640
Gordon,

26:14.640 --> 26:16.600
if the Company murdered
every woman

26:16.600 --> 26:20.479
that JFK had an affair with,
it'd be a goddamn genocide.

26:20.479 --> 26:26.152
Thank you.

26:26.777 --> 26:28.070
- Oh.
- No, no, no.

26:28.070 --> 26:29.989
I-- I just sign for it.

26:30.740 --> 26:31.866
Thank you very much.

26:31.866 --> 26:35.870
If you have money,
join Metropolitan.

26:35.870 --> 26:38.039
You have brains,
you join Cosmos,

26:38.039 --> 26:40.374
if you have neither,
you join the University Club.

26:40.374 --> 26:43.878
I belong to all three.

26:45.963 --> 26:49.175
Of course, you do.

26:50.176 --> 26:53.512
Oh. We have got
some gemstones to sell.

26:53.512 --> 26:54.805
Yes, indeed.

26:58.809 --> 27:03.356
Gentlemen. Gentlemen.
Come in! Sit, sit down.

27:05.399 --> 27:10.279
Uh, we have here the fruits
of your magnificent labors.

27:10.279 --> 27:11.989
Are those the transcripts?

27:11.989 --> 27:14.033
Indeed they are.

27:14.033 --> 27:15.826
Shall we dive in?

27:15.826 --> 27:17.703
Hmm.
"Page one.

27:17.703 --> 27:19.080
Phone conversation.

27:19.080 --> 27:23.876
Tuesday, June 6th, 2:13 p.m.

27:23.876 --> 27:27.713
Secretary, 'I told him
I wanted it curly

27:27.713 --> 27:31.008
but long,
like Maria Schneider.'

27:31.008 --> 27:34.595
Voice, 'I told you
to go to my guy.'

27:34.595 --> 27:37.681
Secretary, 'Instead,
he chops it all off,

27:37.681 --> 27:40.434
and now,
I look like Shelley Winters!'

27:40.434 --> 27:44.563
Voice, 'Shelly Winters?'
Secretary, 'Shelly Winters--'"

27:44.563 --> 27:46.315
Uh, sorry to interrupt, John,

27:46.816 --> 27:48.651
is that the bug

27:48.651 --> 27:50.903
- from O'Brien's secretary?
- Correct.

27:50.903 --> 27:53.781
Why don't we jump ahead
to the bug on O'Brien's phone?

27:53.781 --> 27:56.659
Um, get to the meat
and potatoes.

27:56.659 --> 27:58.786
Yeah. Let's skip this.

27:58.786 --> 28:03.290
Uh, mm, mm, hmm, yes.

28:04.333 --> 28:07.461
Oh. Uh, this one is,
uh, "Inoperative."

28:08.337 --> 28:09.422
No.

28:10.714 --> 28:13.092
What about the bug
in the smoke detector

28:13.092 --> 28:14.468
in O'Brien's office?

28:14.468 --> 28:15.594
Excellent question.

28:15.594 --> 28:18.556
Yeah, this one is actually
my favorite one.

28:18.556 --> 28:20.224
Okay.
Where is it?

28:20.224 --> 28:21.809
Oh, yes. Here we go.

28:21.809 --> 28:23.352
Uh...

28:23.352 --> 28:25.229
Also inoperative.
Oh!

28:25.229 --> 28:28.107
What?
- Sorry, "Inoperative"?

28:29.191 --> 28:31.819
- Inoperative.
- The opposite of operative.

28:31.819 --> 28:32.987
It did not operate.

28:32.987 --> 28:34.447
The only working microphone

28:34.447 --> 28:37.199
that you and your team planted
is the one on the phone

28:37.199 --> 28:40.494
of the secretary who now looks
like Shelley Winters.

28:40.494 --> 28:42.621
You gentlemen should know
I've briefed the president

28:42.621 --> 28:43.831
on the haircut situation,

28:43.831 --> 28:45.374
and we think
this could be the thing

28:45.374 --> 28:46.792
that swings the election.

28:47.751 --> 28:49.253
Thanks for stopping by.

28:49.253 --> 28:52.298
For the record,
I did not want to hire McCord.

28:52.298 --> 28:53.883
You made us hire him.

28:53.883 --> 28:57.136
- And I want that on the record.
- What record?

28:57.136 --> 28:58.679
No one's keeping records
of this shit.

28:58.679 --> 29:00.473
What about the files
they photographed?

29:00.473 --> 29:03.017
Anything Cuban? Russian?
Any-- any dirt at all?

29:03.017 --> 29:06.896
No. Nothing. Zero.
Project OPAL, my ass.

29:06.896 --> 29:10.524
You should call it Project TURD.
Put that on the record, Gordon.

29:10.524 --> 29:11.484
Hang on.

29:11.484 --> 29:12.860
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

29:12.860 --> 29:14.778
There is one idea
we didn't pitch you.

29:15.571 --> 29:17.740
It's cheap but devastating.

29:17.740 --> 29:20.034
With the ability to bury
McGovern once and for all.

29:20.034 --> 29:21.994
No, I-- I think it's too risky.

29:21.994 --> 29:24.038
Mitchell does not need
to hear it.

29:24.038 --> 29:26.040
Hey! Hey! I will be the judge

29:26.040 --> 29:27.833
as to whether
or not Mitchell hears it.

29:30.461 --> 29:32.963
So then these filthy hippies,

29:32.963 --> 29:35.007
you know, covered
in McGovern buttons,

29:35.007 --> 29:38.719
they just piss,
all over the hotel carpet,

29:38.719 --> 29:40.471
in the presidential suite.

29:40.471 --> 29:42.973
They piss all over the carpet?
Like a fire hose!

29:42.973 --> 29:45.309
Like a river of hippie piss.

29:45.309 --> 29:46.852
And all in front
of the cameras.

29:46.852 --> 29:48.354
Right there,
in front of Cronkite.

29:49.313 --> 29:52.107
It's a classic false flag
and cheap.

29:52.107 --> 29:54.068
- Really cheap.
- Under a million dollars?

29:54.068 --> 29:57.154
- Price of a case of beer!
- Or a marijuana cigarette!

30:01.492 --> 30:02.493
Uh...

30:04.036 --> 30:07.414
Do you know
who's got that suite booked

30:07.414 --> 30:08.624
the day after McGovern?

30:08.624 --> 30:11.460
No. But I am sure
we will be hearing about it.

30:11.460 --> 30:14.338
Poor bastard.

30:14.338 --> 30:15.381
I'll spare you the wait.

30:16.799 --> 30:18.092
It's me.

30:19.301 --> 30:23.138
I'm staying in that suite
for our convention, you idiots!

30:23.138 --> 30:25.683
And I don't want
any goddamn drug addicts

30:25.683 --> 30:28.060
pissing all over my carpet!

30:28.060 --> 30:30.854
♪ (JAZZ MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

30:30.854 --> 30:32.731
Dorothy may have been right

30:32.731 --> 30:35.359
about Pissers.

30:36.652 --> 30:39.655
Magruder knew
Mitchell's itinerary. He had to.

30:40.656 --> 30:43.409
Son of a bitch
let us hang ourselves.

30:46.704 --> 30:48.372
The president is a good man.

30:49.290 --> 30:50.541
But between you and me,

30:50.541 --> 30:53.919
I worry about some of the people
with whom he surrounds himself.

30:53.919 --> 30:55.129
Hmm.

30:57.506 --> 31:00.551
Shit!

31:00.551 --> 31:02.761
♪ (PIANO PLAYING) ♪

31:02.761 --> 31:05.389
Howard, please.
Lakewood, they called twice.

31:05.389 --> 31:07.558
I will pay them.
I promise.

31:07.558 --> 31:10.603
It might be time
for some new luggage.

31:17.776 --> 31:21.739
Has he been taking lessons?
He's quite good.

31:21.739 --> 31:25.326
Both your sons
are talented musicians.

31:25.326 --> 31:26.493
Of course.

31:27.536 --> 31:28.621
Yeah.

31:35.836 --> 31:38.964
- What if I came to Paris?
- Is Papa coming?

31:38.964 --> 31:40.466
What?
Sure, kiddo!

31:40.466 --> 31:41.967
We could go to Rue Cler,

31:41.967 --> 31:46.055
stop by that little chocolatier,
if it's still there.

31:46.055 --> 31:49.850
It'll be just like
when we first started dating.

31:49.850 --> 31:53.604
Hmm. You do know David
and Kevan are coming, also.

31:55.397 --> 31:57.650
Do you not want me to come?

31:57.650 --> 32:01.195
Of course, I want you to come. Okay.

32:03.572 --> 32:07.409
Let me go get
my dusty old suitcase.

32:15.459 --> 32:17.878
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

32:18.796 --> 32:19.797
Gordon.

32:21.465 --> 32:23.801
- Gordon.
- Fuck you, Jeb.

32:23.801 --> 32:25.636
Good morning.

32:26.637 --> 32:28.013
How are you?

32:28.013 --> 32:29.264
Fuck you, Jeb.

32:29.264 --> 32:30.808
I heard you the first time.

32:30.808 --> 32:32.518
May I have a moment
of your time please?

32:33.268 --> 32:34.269
My office.

32:36.313 --> 32:37.815
♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

32:37.815 --> 32:39.983
Okay, somebody needs
to clean this mess up.

32:39.983 --> 32:42.736
That dumbbell McCord needs
to fix his bugs.

32:42.736 --> 32:44.363
And you need
to photograph everything

32:44.363 --> 32:47.199
in the bottom left drawer
of O'Brien's desk.

32:48.325 --> 32:49.368
Which drawer?

32:50.160 --> 32:51.578
Bottom left.

32:52.663 --> 32:54.123
Why?

32:54.123 --> 32:55.874
What's in the drawer?

32:55.874 --> 32:58.377
That's what he wants you
to find out!

33:01.505 --> 33:03.799
You want us to break in
a fourth time?

33:03.799 --> 33:05.592
Wait, what do you mean
a fourth time?

33:06.719 --> 33:08.053
Nothing. Spy talk.

33:09.930 --> 33:10.931
Got it.

33:15.686 --> 33:18.480
No. No, Gordon.

33:18.480 --> 33:21.358
I don't care what
that little glad-handing

33:21.358 --> 33:24.820
frat boy thinks.
No! That's my final word.

33:28.490 --> 33:30.993
Should I pack a raincoat?

33:32.286 --> 33:34.204
What did Gordon want?

33:34.204 --> 33:35.622
Nothing.

33:35.622 --> 33:38.250
Well, he wants us
to hit the DNC again.

33:38.250 --> 33:40.627
I have to tell you, Howard,

33:40.627 --> 33:43.422
this is sounding more and more
like the Bay of Pigs.

33:50.179 --> 33:51.221
Believe me.

33:52.181 --> 33:53.182
I know.

33:54.016 --> 33:56.268
♪ (PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

33:56.268 --> 33:58.270
You heard me.
I-- I told Gordon.

33:58.729 --> 33:59.813
I'm out.

34:03.650 --> 34:04.693
I'm done.

34:14.411 --> 34:16.288
Oh, God.

34:16.288 --> 34:19.082
I left my passport in the safe
at the White House.

34:19.082 --> 34:23.420
I'll be back in a jiffy.
Pack my new brown loafers.

34:23.962 --> 34:25.005
Hey, kiddo.

34:26.465 --> 34:27.508
Where's Papa going?

34:27.508 --> 34:29.218
Isn't he coming
to Paris with us?

34:30.427 --> 34:33.305
Absolutely, yes, sweetie.

34:42.523 --> 34:44.608
Knock, knock.

34:44.608 --> 34:49.029
Gordon.

34:49.029 --> 34:50.280
Howard.

34:53.283 --> 34:56.119
I told you, I'm out.

34:56.119 --> 35:00.290
I'm going to Paris
with my family.

35:00.290 --> 35:03.418
Fuck Paris!
Your country needs you.

35:03.418 --> 35:07.673
Look, I'm sorry Gordon.
We can't do this.

35:07.673 --> 35:11.927
We burned through our budget.
There is nothing left.

35:11.927 --> 35:13.470
I sent a bunch
of old campaign checks

35:13.470 --> 35:14.721
to Macho.
He's going to rinse them

35:14.721 --> 35:16.682
in his Mexican bank account
and bring the cash up

35:16.682 --> 35:19.226
with the boys. We are flush.
We are ready to go.

35:19.226 --> 35:22.354
This does not feel right, Gordon.

35:22.354 --> 35:27.067
Jesus. It feels slapdash. Risky.

35:27.067 --> 35:30.112
- ♪ (TENSE MUSIC PLAYING) ♪
- So then we send the Cubans in.

35:30.112 --> 35:31.572
We wait back
in the Command Center,

35:31.572 --> 35:32.698
you and I.

35:36.410 --> 35:38.871
I have done that before.

35:39.454 --> 35:41.290
Never again.

35:47.337 --> 35:48.380
Never.

35:51.967 --> 35:54.261
So, that's it? Hmm?

35:54.261 --> 35:56.555
You're just going
to let them win? Huh?

35:56.555 --> 36:00.017
Who, Gordon? Who?

36:00.642 --> 36:03.896
The Democrats? Fuck 'em.

36:03.896 --> 36:06.440
If they elect McGovern,
then they deserve

36:06.440 --> 36:08.191
all that's coming to them.

36:08.191 --> 36:10.777
I was talking
about those son of a bitches

36:10.777 --> 36:13.947
from the Cosmos Club.
Angleton, the...

36:15.532 --> 36:16.658
other prick.

36:17.784 --> 36:20.871
Ones who hung you out
to dry, then walked away,

36:20.871 --> 36:23.040
giggling scot-free.

36:23.040 --> 36:26.627
I saw the way that
they high-hatted you.

36:26.627 --> 36:29.713
I've been dealing with bullies
like that my whole life.

36:31.924 --> 36:34.176
That's why I left
the Bureau.

36:35.677 --> 36:37.137
And now, you and I are working

36:37.137 --> 36:40.599
for the President
of the United States of America.

36:44.144 --> 36:46.980
And if we can just deliver him
one election...

36:46.980 --> 36:51.109
...who knows?

36:52.152 --> 36:54.655
You know,
the President may say to you,

36:54.655 --> 36:57.741
“Howard, what do you want?”

36:59.576 --> 37:00.619
And you can say...

37:02.162 --> 37:03.205
“Mr. President...

37:04.873 --> 37:06.583
I want to be CIA Director."

37:08.001 --> 37:11.004
And he will say, "Done."

37:11.004 --> 37:14.091
And all those
little sons of bitches...

37:15.425 --> 37:18.178
they will be licking
your loafers.

37:18.178 --> 37:21.139
And then you can send them out
to pasture, writing PR copy

37:21.139 --> 37:22.307
for Mullen.

37:23.558 --> 37:24.601
Gordon...

37:26.269 --> 37:27.479
you know
that's not how it works.

37:27.479 --> 37:31.149
It works any way that
the president wants it to work.

37:31.149 --> 37:33.860
It is about proximity to power.

37:34.820 --> 37:37.698
And you and I are as close
as it gets.

37:37.698 --> 37:41.201
What-- what's your big gripe
about JFK? Hmm?

37:41.201 --> 37:43.662
It's that when shit got hairy...

37:43.662 --> 37:46.748
...that coward got cold feet

37:46.748 --> 37:49.876
and did not do what was right
at the Bay of Pigs.

37:49.876 --> 37:52.713
You're better than that.
You're better than him.

37:57.384 --> 37:59.845
Thank you, partner.

37:59.845 --> 38:04.182
♪ (WHIMSICAL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

38:06.852 --> 38:10.856
And head right to Géricault's
<i>Raft of the Medusa.</i>

38:10.856 --> 38:12.899
Do not waste your time

38:12.899 --> 38:15.861
on the <i>Mona Lisa.</i>
She's overrated

38:15.861 --> 38:17.696
and-- and for tourists.

38:17.696 --> 38:20.574
I wrote it all down, Papa.

38:22.951 --> 38:25.078
Are you sure you can't come?

38:25.078 --> 38:28.957
Um, maybe I can try
to meet you there.

38:28.957 --> 38:32.711
- It's fine, Howard. Really.
- All right. Shove over, squirt.

38:32.711 --> 38:35.714
Okay, I will pay
the Lakewood dues. I promise.

38:39.926 --> 38:41.386
Please be careful.

38:41.386 --> 38:42.554
I'll look after him.

38:42.554 --> 38:44.181
Bye, Mama!

38:44.181 --> 38:45.640
See you in a month!

38:45.640 --> 38:47.184
<i>Au revoir, ma chérie!</i>

38:49.644 --> 38:53.065
So, uh, Saint's band finally
has a name.

38:53.065 --> 38:55.859
We're called Daybreak.

38:55.859 --> 38:59.738
They actually have a gig tonight
if we all want to go?

39:01.531 --> 39:02.866
- Uh...
- It's fine if you can't.

39:02.866 --> 39:06.161
Of course,
I want to, uh...

39:06.161 --> 39:08.455
- But you have to work.
- But I have to...

39:09.498 --> 39:10.624
- work.
- Right.

39:10.624 --> 39:13.460
Come on.

39:13.460 --> 39:20.050
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

40:21.194 --> 40:23.697
I don't understand.
I taped the lock myself.

40:23.697 --> 40:25.198
Think it was a guard?

40:26.491 --> 40:28.118
I don't know.

40:28.118 --> 40:30.036
Could have been
a mailman or something.

40:31.496 --> 40:33.957
What do we do?
- Leave it. Let's go.

40:33.957 --> 40:35.250
- Leave it.
<i>- Vámonos.</i>

40:38.503 --> 40:39.963
Thought it was
taped over before.

40:39.963 --> 40:41.923
<i>Senator Hubert Humphrey's camp</i>

40:41.923 --> 40:44.092
<i>today predicted
that McGovern would fall</i>

40:44.092 --> 40:45.802
<i>more than 180 votes short</i>

40:45.802 --> 40:47.345
<i>on the convention's
first ballot,</i>

40:47.345 --> 40:49.556
<i>thereafter would fail
to pick up any major...</i>

40:49.556 --> 40:51.057
Those are the pants
you're wearing?

40:52.392 --> 40:54.644
What's wrong with them?

40:54.644 --> 40:58.815
Just s... so shiny.
It's not an Italian wedding.

40:58.815 --> 41:01.818
Jesus, Gordon,
we're in the Command Post.

41:01.818 --> 41:03.069
What does it matter?

41:03.069 --> 41:07.073
What if we were forced to hide,
and the only thing

41:07.073 --> 41:10.285
that gave away our position
was the blinding sheen

41:10.285 --> 41:12.329
emanating from your pants?

41:12.329 --> 41:14.915
Are you ordering me
to change my pants?

41:14.915 --> 41:20.170
No. Simply stating a fact.
That were I wearing such glossy,

41:20.170 --> 41:24.216
saucy pants tonight,
I would change my pants.

41:24.216 --> 41:26.927
Christ.

41:28.970 --> 41:32.265
You know, you complimented
these pants in Miami.

41:35.185 --> 41:37.646
That was Miami.

41:43.610 --> 41:46.029
Not on me.
- The tape on the door was gone.

41:46.029 --> 41:47.072
Security?

41:47.072 --> 41:48.114
<i>No sé.</i>

41:48.114 --> 41:50.617
Whatever. We couldn't get in.

41:50.617 --> 41:51.785
What do we do, boss?

41:52.535 --> 41:53.662
Sharp pants.

41:57.207 --> 41:58.917
We abort.

41:58.917 --> 42:01.044
This operation is over.

42:01.044 --> 42:03.213
Shit, I would have gone
to De Diego's daughter's wedding

42:03.213 --> 42:05.507
if I knew we weren't going
to go in again.

42:05.507 --> 42:06.925
I wasn't invited.

42:07.842 --> 42:10.178
It was small. It's just family.

42:11.763 --> 42:14.474
Hang on a minute.
That tape thing, with the door,

42:14.474 --> 42:17.143
- could you do that again?
- I don't see why not.

42:17.143 --> 42:19.354
I said abort.

42:19.354 --> 42:23.275
Mr. Cold Feet.
Fuckin' Kennedy all over again.

42:23.275 --> 42:24.776
Fuckin' Bay of Pigs.

42:24.776 --> 42:27.237
I don't wanna hear
another goddamn peep out of you,

42:27.237 --> 42:29.531
Frank. This is my call.

42:29.531 --> 42:31.408
The hell it is.

42:32.909 --> 42:35.453
We were ordered to take
that drawer,

42:35.453 --> 42:39.207
and we're going to do it,
whether you like it or not.

42:39.207 --> 42:41.251
Gentlemen, do you want
to walk away

42:41.251 --> 42:42.836
with your tails
between your legs,

42:42.836 --> 42:46.256
or do you want to fly
with El Halcón?

42:47.674 --> 42:52.721
Hey, you have done enough
for this country.

42:53.388 --> 42:54.556
In the war.

42:55.265 --> 42:56.933
In Cuba.

42:56.933 --> 43:00.895
You have nothing to prove
to me, to anyone.

43:00.895 --> 43:03.606
Least of all, to El Halcón.

43:03.606 --> 43:06.276
Last I checked,
this is not Cuba.

43:06.276 --> 43:09.029
This is a democracy.
I say we vote.

43:09.029 --> 43:10.947
Up or down,
in or out, yes or no.

43:10.947 --> 43:13.950
Whoever wants to go in,
raise your hand.

43:16.536 --> 43:18.580
♪ (TENSE MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

43:18.580 --> 43:21.207
- Et tu, Musculito?
<i>- Acere.</i>

43:21.207 --> 43:25.211
My wife just served me
with divorce papers, so...

43:25.211 --> 43:27.505
So? Is that a yes or a no?

43:27.505 --> 43:30.008
It's a "We don't get paid
if we don't get in,

43:30.008 --> 43:33.136
my life is shit,
and I need the money." Sorry.

43:34.846 --> 43:38.850
- Macho?
- No way. I'm with you, boss.

43:40.143 --> 43:41.561
Me, too.

43:41.561 --> 43:43.229
Then put your hand down.

43:44.939 --> 43:48.068
- Frank, in or out?
- Jill St. John canceled on me,

43:48.068 --> 43:50.070
so I guess I'm...
I'm free tonight.

43:50.070 --> 43:51.404
Outstanding.

43:52.489 --> 43:56.326
Jim, we'll let you
be the tiebreaker.

43:57.160 --> 43:58.953
I wanna get those mics working.

43:58.953 --> 44:00.997
It's a point
of professional pride.

44:01.956 --> 44:02.957
I'm in.

44:04.709 --> 44:05.752
Okay. We do it.

44:05.752 --> 44:07.253
Fantastic.
All right.

44:11.091 --> 44:14.260
Oh, uh, hey, Macho.

44:14.260 --> 44:17.514
There's a mailbox right inside
near the garage door,

44:17.514 --> 44:19.557
can you drop this
on your way in?

44:19.557 --> 44:21.393
I'll be stuck here all night.

44:21.393 --> 44:24.062
You know, <i>acere,</i>
it's going to be fine.

44:24.062 --> 44:27.732
Yeah.

44:27.732 --> 44:30.693
<i>-¡Cuba libre!
-¡Viva President Nixon!</i>

44:31.486 --> 44:37.450
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

44:42.247 --> 44:43.623
Okay, tighten this.

44:44.499 --> 44:46.084
- In here.
- That's plenty tight.

44:46.084 --> 44:47.961
- I already tightened it.
- Tighter.

45:29.919 --> 45:32.088
♪ (MUSIC FADES) ♪

45:32.088 --> 45:39.012
Thirty-six, 35, 34, 33.
- Do you ever miss a day?

45:39.012 --> 45:41.890
Negative. Thirty.

45:41.890 --> 45:43.850
<i>Unit Two to Unit One.</i>

45:43.850 --> 45:45.226
<i>Unit Two to Unit One.</i>

45:47.103 --> 45:48.188
<i>We're in.</i>

45:48.188 --> 45:50.440
<i>Unit One to Unit Two. Copy that.</i>

45:51.107 --> 45:52.317
<i>Outstanding.</i>

45:59.282 --> 46:02.827
- Oh.
- Oh, finally.

46:08.625 --> 46:09.626
So...

46:11.294 --> 46:14.380
who really killed JFK?

46:15.882 --> 46:17.634
Oh, Christ.

46:17.634 --> 46:22.889
I think Cord Meyer knew
who really killed JFK.

46:23.723 --> 46:25.975
And then they killed his wife

46:25.975 --> 46:28.394
so that he would stay quiet
about it.

46:32.732 --> 46:34.692
What do you think of that?

46:34.692 --> 46:38.071
I think
you're a far smarter man

46:38.071 --> 46:40.490
than anyone gives you
credit for.

46:41.491 --> 46:42.534
Thank you.

46:50.959 --> 46:52.460
Come to think of it,

46:52.460 --> 46:56.631
weren't you CIA station chief
in Mexico when Oswald was there?

46:56.631 --> 46:58.591
Oh, God. Gordon.

46:58.591 --> 47:04.597
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

47:25.243 --> 47:28.496
Hey, Bobby, it's Wills.
I'm in the garage.

47:28.496 --> 47:30.373
Yeah, I got a situation
down here.

47:31.207 --> 47:32.458
I'm coming up.

47:32.458 --> 47:36.254
Where were you
on November 22nd, 1963?

47:37.422 --> 47:40.383
I was with Dorothy
at a Chinese restaurant,

47:40.383 --> 47:42.385
Downtown DC.

47:43.970 --> 47:45.972
Like I told
the Warren Commission.

47:51.728 --> 47:54.480
<i>Unit Three to Unit One.
Come in, over.</i>

47:55.565 --> 47:57.275
This is Unit One, over.

47:57.275 --> 48:00.361
<i>Are our guys
dressed like hippies? Over.</i>

48:00.361 --> 48:04.365
No. Our guys are wearing suits.
Why? Over.

48:04.365 --> 48:07.660
There are three guys
dressed like hippies on six,

48:07.660 --> 48:10.079
and they've got flashlights. Over.

48:11.581 --> 48:12.790
Cleaning staff?

48:13.499 --> 48:15.001
Hippies? Cleaning?

48:15.918 --> 48:19.380
Uh, probably cleaning staff. Over.

48:22.133 --> 48:23.968
They've got guns. Over.

48:24.802 --> 48:25.803
Cops.

48:27.138 --> 48:29.307
Stay off this channel,
maintain radio silence.

48:29.307 --> 48:31.100
Pack up and get out. Over.

48:31.100 --> 48:34.979
Roger that. Are we going
to try again tomorrow?

48:34.979 --> 48:40.360
- Get them the hell out of there.
- Yes, I know. Come on, Macho.

48:40.360 --> 48:42.695
- Unit One to Unit Two. Come in.
- ♪ (TENSE MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

48:43.946 --> 48:45.657
Unit One to Unit Two. Come in.

48:45.657 --> 48:47.659
Why the hell isn't he answering?

48:47.659 --> 48:50.244
Unit Two to Unit One.
They got us.

48:57.960 --> 49:01.047
Let's sit tight.
We don't know who they are.

49:01.047 --> 49:04.759
Macho
has a room key. To this room.

49:06.803 --> 49:08.680
You get the antenna.
I'm gonna pack the bags.

49:08.680 --> 49:11.849
Fuck! Fuck, fuck, fuck, fuck.

49:11.849 --> 49:17.271
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

49:45.466 --> 49:46.634
What's taking you so long?

49:46.634 --> 49:50.012
- It's too tight!
- You told me to tighten it.

49:51.514 --> 49:54.100
Don't panic!

49:56.686 --> 49:59.313
- Fuck!
- Don't panic!

50:11.784 --> 50:14.287
Come on! Fuck!

